Section 1:
HCR 16 Text skip navigation SENATE PRESIDENT SENATORS COMMITTEES VIDEO/AUDIO DISTRICT MAPS SENATE CLERK SENATE RULES HOUSE SPEAKER DELEGATES COMMITTEES VIDEO/AUDIO DISTRICT MAPS HOUSE CLERK HOUSE RULES HOUSE STAFF JOINT INTERIM COMMITTEES LEGISLATIVE ADMINISTRATOR LEGISLATIVE SERVICES DIVISION PUBLIC INFORMATION LEGISLATIVE AUTOMATED SYSTEMS DIVISION LEGISLATIVE AUDITOR'S OFFICE PERFORMANCE EVALUATION & RESEARCH DIVISION POST AUDIT DIVISION BUDGET DIVISION REGULATORY AND FISCAL AFFAIRS DIVISION CLAIMS COMMISSION CRIME VICTIMS RULE-MAKING REVIEW SPECIAL INVESTIGATIONS JUDICIAL COMP. COMMISSION JOINT RULES STAFF INFO BILL STATUS BILL STATUS BILL TRACKING STATE LAW WEST VIRGINIA CODE ACTS OF THE LEGISLATURE CODE OF 1931 WV CONSTITUTION US CONSTITUTION REPORTS AGENCY REPORTS AGENCY GRANT AWARDS PERFORMANCE EVALUATIONS POST AUDITS EDUCATIONAL CITIZEN’S GUIDE INTERNSHIP PROGRAM PAGE PROGRAM PUBLICATIONS PHOTO GALLERY CAPITOL HISTORY HOW A BILL BECOMES LAW CONTACT SENATE ROSTER HOUSE ROSTER PUBLIC INFO. NEWS RELEASES HELPFUL LINKS Introduced Version House Concurrent Resolution 16 History |  Email Key: Green = existing Code. Red = new code to be enacted HOUSE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION 16(By Delegate Kump)Introduced February 13, 2025; Referred to the Committee on the Judiciary and then rules.]Requesting that the United States Congress pass a proposal to amend the United States Constitution to establish nine as the number of Supreme Court Justices.Whereas, The Supreme Court of the United States of America shall have nine Justices serving at a given time and nine shall be the number serving during any official Term of the Supreme Court; therefore, be it Resolved by the Legislature of West Virginia:That a request is hereby made to the United States Congress to pass a proposal that would set the number of Justices on the Supreme Court of the United States of America at nine, and, be it Further Resolved, That the Clerk of the House forward a copy of this resolution to the President and Vice President of the United States of America, Republican and Democrat leadership in the United States House of Representatives and Senate, all federal legislators who serve West Virginia, and all statewide elected officials in West Virginia. Bill Status  | Bill Tracking  | Legacy WV Code  | Bulletin Board  | District Maps  | Senate Roster  | House Roster  | Live  | Blog  | Jobs  | Links  | Home This Web site is maintained by the West Virginia Legislature's Office of Reference & Information.  | Terms of Use | Webmaster | © 2025 West Virginia Legislature ** Print On Demand Name: Email: Phone:


